AGI - It will be a long process, but Sardinia aims to have a central role, of bridge between Europe and North Africa, > through the birth of the Macroregion of the western Mediterranean, along with Corsica and Balearics. The objective is contained in the proposal of law number 1 of the new regional legislature, signed by the group of Common Horizon, the first signatory to the Councillor for Tourism, Crafts and Commerce, the regional councillor Franco Cuccureddu, coordinator of the party. The text, which contains one of the themes included in the electoral programme > of the centre-left coalition led by Alessandra Todde, was deposited even before the presentation of the new Junta.
&nbsp;
"The main objective of the proposal is to transform the difficulties of insularity into a strong point and as Macroregione to deal directly with the European Union", explained the group leader of Common Horizon, Sandro Porcu, in presenting the proposal this morning in the Regional Council. The central themes are the protection of cultural and linguistic identity, fiscal policy of advantage and compensation of the costs of insularity, mobility and territorial continuity, cooperation, environmental protection (in particular maritime) and peace.
&nbsp;
"Our proposal was born of a work that since 2009 carried out the Isprom, the Institute of Studies and Programmes for the Mediterranean born in 1972 and financed by the Region" (presied by former parliamentarian Francesco Sanna), Cuccureddu recalled, which considers the road of Macroregione the only instrument possible to attribute to Sardinia the possibility to deal directly with the EU, even to tear functional derogations > to overcome the statute That hypothesis, which would involve six States - Italy, France, Spain, Morocco, Algeria and Tunisia - and three islands, would be the fifth Macroregion activated in Europe since the start of the EU's macro-regional strategy. The first was the Macroregion of the Baltic Sea, followed by the Danube in 2010, the Adriatic-Ionian in 2014 and the Alpine in 2015.
&nbsp;
&nbsp; The bill, five articles in all >, is open to support all other political forces and will be assigned to the Third Board of Directors. Cuccureddu hopes it will be approved by the end of the year. The presentation was attended by Giovanni Lobrano, the former president of the Molise Region, Giovanni Di Stasi, among the proponents of the Adriatic-Ionian Macroregion, Francesco Sanna and Tore Cherchi, Vice-President of Isprom. The chronoprogramme drawn from the text previews first understood with Corsica and Balearics and a project of macroregional strategy to insular promotion entrusted to a Table of design> that should be constituted from Region, Isprom and the universities of Cagliari and Sassari, than from 26 April 2023 already have an agreement with the universities of Corsica and Balearics. Within 24 months there will be a total proposal, in agreement with the other two islands. The Table shall produce a report to be sent to the Third Committee of the Regional Council and to the Council of Local Authorities. The text, finally, hypotheses two research grants for Sardinian universities for a total of 250 thousand euros.

